abstract: Nearly every city agency has more workers now than when Mayor Bill de Blasio took office, and there’s been a surge in civilian hiring in law enforcement.

lead_paragraph: After serving a tour in the sticky rice and fruit fields of northeast Thailand for the Peace Corps, Leanne Spaulding landed a job at a Virginia-based trade association, working her way to a master’s degree from Duke University in environmental management.

abstract: The lack of an African-American challenger in the mayoral race highlights the absence of a rising generation of black politicians in New York.
snippet: The lack of an African-American challenger in the mayoral race highlights the absence of a rising generation of black politicians in New York.
lead_paragraph: Among New Yorkers in the brownstone-occupying territories, which is to say in many of the places that elected him in the first place, it is common to encounter a sense of bewildered frustration at the notion that Mayor Bill de Blasio faces almost no opposition in his race for a second term. How is this possible when rates of homelessness have risen, when towers are going up in communities that don’t want them, when so many seem to have so little enthusiasm for him on a personal level?

abstract: The office messaging company is not yet profitable, but new funding could raise its valuation to $5 billion as it faces rivals like Microsoft’s Teams.
snippet: The office messaging company is not yet profitable, but new funding could raise its valuation to $5 billion as it faces rivals like Microsoft’s Teams.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Slack, an office messaging company, is in talks to raise around $500 million at a valuation around $5 billion, according to two people with knowledge of the discussions, who were not authorized to speak publicly about the financing.

abstract: After years of stagnation and political wrangling, a vast new commercial and residential complex will come to the Lower East Side of Manhattan.
snippet: After years of stagnation and political wrangling, a vast new commercial and residential complex will come to the Lower East Side of Manhattan.
lead_paragraph: When the first phase of construction is finally finished this fall, the enormous Essex Crossing development will begin to transform the Lower East Side of Manhattan: luxury condominiums, a vast underground market with local vendors, a senior center, a museum, a public park, a bowling alley and the first multiplex movie theater in the neighborhood.

abstract: In 2013, Bill de Blasio rallied from outsider to victor in the mayoral race. Now, he is the overwhelming favorite in his quest for another term.
snippet: In 2013, Bill de Blasio rallied from outsider to victor in the mayoral race. Now, he is the overwhelming favorite in his quest for another term.
lead_paragraph: More than four years after officially announcing his mayoral run, Mayor Bill de Blasio seeks another term in a political environment that could not be more different.

abstract: Mayor Bill de Blasio wants to retain control over city schools. In exchange, Republicans want more charter schools and Democrats want tax increases.
snippet: Mayor Bill de Blasio wants to retain control over city schools. In exchange, Republicans want more charter schools and Democrats want tax increases.
lead_paragraph: ALBANY — Each spring, Mayor Bill de Blasio does a dance with the State Legislature to extend his control of the city’s schools, and each time, the Democrat-led State Assembly happily assents.

lead_paragraph: It was the testimony of a once-obscure former law enforcement official. Before the Senate Select Committee on Intelligence. At 10 in the morning. On a workday.

abstract: A dispute over the Puerto Rican Day Parade exposed a growing rift between Mayor Bill de Blasio and Melissa Mark-Viverito, his top Hispanic ally.
snippet: A dispute over the Puerto Rican Day Parade exposed a growing rift between Mayor Bill de Blasio and Melissa Mark-Viverito, his top Hispanic ally.
lead_paragraph: The past week was to be a feel-good time for Mayor Bill de Blasio and other politicians to connect with Hispanic voters, culminating in Sunday’s Puerto Rican Day Parade.
